post_text: The Colman-Egan School District is hiring route bus drivers and substitutes. Duties will include daily route during the school year along with driving for some school related events throughout the year. As a substitute you would fill in when another bus driver can't drive. Successful applicants must hold or pass a Class "B" Driving Endorsement. If you do not have a CDL the school will help you obtain one. Please forward a letter of interest stating experience, qualifications and references to Brian.Corlett@k12.sd.us.

post_text:
This is to update everyone regarding the Colman-Egan School Board Election.

The new date for our School Board Election is June 23rd, 2020. It will be held at the Colman-Egan School front entrance. Polling times will be 7:00 am to 7:00 pm. Publications of the upcoming School Board Election will also be advertised in the newspaper as required.

I would like to mention that absentee voting is available to all registered voters. You can either contact me at luann.smith@k12.sd.us to get an absentee application or you can also get one from the Secretary of State website at sdsos.gov/elections-voting/. It is the first option on the red ribbon at the top of the page (Request Absentee Ballot). It will be the second bullet on the page (Download and print an Absentee Ballot Application).

Please message our Facebook page or Contact any of our Colman Fire Dept personnel.

post_text: Band Time, Choir Time, Fun Time (BTCTFT).... what is it? The music officers and I met at the beginning of the school year and I shared with them that I would really like to put together some type of get together each month for our music students. "Making Music, Making Friends" An opportunity to just plain have fun, spend time with friends and maybe experience something they would not normally have the opportunity to do. They came up with BTCTFT! We've had movie nights, game nights, Halloween parties (haunted hall included), Thanksgiving meal and today something new! We went ice skating!!! It was definitely a new experience for most of the kids and although they spent a fair amount of time not on their feet they seemed to have a great time!!!! Thank you to all that purchased World's Finest Chocolate which helped pay for admission and skate rentals! PS I have great videos too but it won't let me post them! I'll try to get them to your kids.

post_text: Congratulations to Colman-Egan Senior Allison Olson for being chosen to participate in the 2020 South Dakota High School All State Band! Allison, along with hundreds of other students from across the state) performed at a live audition and completed a written terms test in order to be considered for the elite band. She will attend a three day event in Mitchell which will conclude with concert that is open to the public. This is Allison's 3rd year as a high school all state member.

post_text: Congratulations to the One-Act Participants. This short season was fantastic! You have shown teamwork, effort, and growth. Half of our cast was a first-year participant. Yesterday at the One-Act Region IIIA competition, three students were awarded an "Outstanding" for their roles in "Passing Periods at Pomegranate Prep". Those students include: Zeke Wendell, Jordan Wittrock, and Torry Harding, While CEHS did not advance to state, their performance at regions was the best yet. We cordially invite everyone in the CEHS community to see our last show Thursday, January 30th 7 p.m., at Colman-Egan High School. This 30-minute comedy is free and open to the public.

post_text: This week the Colman-Egan 3rd Graders read "Aero and Officer Mike" by Joan Plummer Russell, an informational text about a K9 Officer and his partner. The students were fascinated by the duties and skill sets a K9 Officer needs to train for. We are very fortunate to have a K9 Officer and handler near us. A very special Thank You to Officer Rupe, Tu Sox, Sheriff Wellman, and Deputy Brakke for visiting us and answering all our questions! There is a short video of Tu Sox at work in the comments :)

post_text: Mark your calendars! The Oral Interp team will be hosting a local showcase at the school at 1:30 PM on Sunday, November 3rd. Anyone is welcome to come and watch! The students would love your support. Light snacks and refreshments will be provided.

post_text: I think our first music department Halloween Bash was definitely a success! We hosted over 50 music students. They nibbled on tasty treats, watched movies and got to experience the haunted hallway multiple times! A huge shout out to Bridgette, Allison, Jenna, Karisma, Jordan and Jack who spent hours decorating and even more hours entertaining. You guys are amazing! And thanks to Jenna and Allison for baking the yummy treats. Congratulations to our costume winners - Tobey and Anya. Tons of awesome outfits!!! Thank you to all who made the day a success!

post_text: Today was the Dakota Valley Conference C C Meet held at Sunrise Ridge Golf Course. For the Varsity Girls Reese finished 2, Abby 6, and Presley 13 out of 33. As a team, the ladies took home third place. For the JV Girls, Kayla finished 10 out of 22. The JV Boys, Jackson finished 6, and Sutton 7 out of 34. Great job today C - E Hawks.
